1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper proposes a new iterative image reconstruction algorithm for electrical capacitance tomography, which is a technique used for imaging of multiphase systems. This involves processing and analyzing images, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.IM (Image and Video Processing) - The paper deals with image reconstruction using electrical capacitance tomography, which is a type of image processing. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses compressive sensing techniques for image reconstruction, which is a topic related to information theory. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper proposes a new algorithm for image reconstruction, which involves numerical methods and optimization techniques. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - Although less likely, this paper could also fall under the category of social and information networks as electrical capacitance tomography is used in various industrial and medical applications, which involve the analysis and processing of networked data.
